uid><pubDate>2026-05-10T01:07:15+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130982667,imgsize-96020.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Russia grateful to US for talks': Putin says Ukraine conflict ‘coming to an end’]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130982369.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/russia-grateful-to-us-for-talks-ukraine-conflict-coming-to-an-end-vladimir-putin-awaits-kyiv-response-on-pow-swap/articleshow/130982369.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/russia-grateful-to-us-for-talks-ukraine-conflict-coming-to-an-end-vladimir-putin-awaits-kyiv-response-on-pow-swap/articleshow/130982369.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-10T00:17:05+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130982380,imgsize-16748.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Plane with 231 flyers runs over jaywalker, engine catches fire]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130982606.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A Frontier Airlines flight bound for Los Angeles struck and killed a pedestrian who had jumped the airport's perimeter fence and was crossing the runway during takeoff. The incident sparked an engine fire, prompting the evacuation of 224 passengers and seven crew members. Minor injuries were reported among passengers, and authorities are investigating the fatal event.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/plane-with-231-flyers-runs-over-jaywalker-engine-catches-fire/articleshow/130982606.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/plane-with-231-flyers-runs-over-jaywalker-engine-catches-fire/articleshow/130982606.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-10T00:53:33+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130982622,imgsize-26410.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Keir Starmer appoints former Labour PM Gordon Brown as adviser after election flop]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130982445.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Following significant local election losses, Labour leader Keir Starmer has appointed former Prime Minister Gordon Brown as a special envoy. This move comes amidst calls for Starmer's resignation from some party MPs, while voters express dissatisfaction with economic issues and immigration. Reform UK and the Greens have seen substantial gains in the polls.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/keir-starmer-appoints-gordon-brown-as-adviser-after-election-flop/articleshow/130982445.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/keir-starmer-appoints-gordon-brown-as-adviser-after-election-flop/articleshow/130982445.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-10T00:27:19+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Naomi Canton</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130982476,imgsize-38272.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Vatican softens towards LGBTQ+ Catholics]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/130982631.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Pope Leo XIV's Vatican is signaling a nuanced approach to LGBTQ+ Catholics, embracing dialogue while maintaining traditional stances on same-sex blessings. A recent Vatican report highlighted testimonies from gay Catholics, emphasizing social justice over sexual morality. This move has drawn praise from advocates and criticism from conservatives, underscoring the ongoing internal church debate.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/vatican-softens-towards-lgbtq-catholics/articleshow/130982631.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/vatican-softens-towards-lgbtq-catholics/articleshow/130982631.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-05-10T00:58:10+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-130982647,imgsize-20604.cms"/></item></channel></rss>